# Performance Standards

- This is a stack-specific rule file for Node.js runtime behavior.
- Optimize only after identifying the hot path, bottleneck, or operational limit being addressed.
- Keep request and event handlers non-blocking. Avoid CPU-heavy work, large synchronous loops, and blocking I/O on hot paths.
- For large payloads or long-running transfers, prefer streams and backpressure-aware APIs over buffering entire datasets in memory.
- Reuse shared serializers, validators, and transport helpers on hot paths instead of rebuilding equivalent logic per feature.
- Avoid accidental quadratic work in controllers, handlers, serializers, and mappers when processing lists or streams.
- When a change targets performance-sensitive behavior, document the assumption being optimized and verify the result with measurement or profiling.
